<br>
The bottom line is random is there as the failsafe. It comes up if everyone is pretty evenly matched, or can't decide what goes to who. It removes the need for a loot officer of any kind, and as loot officers and the like generally get fouled up at some point, that's not a bad thing. It also means there isn't an officer getting headaches about keeping track of everyone's gear.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for the robe, who do you think would deserve an item more, someone who already has something like it or someone who doesn't? We're assuming they both put forth the same efforts for the guild and are the same level, as well as both being in the guild for about the same time. Is there an incentive for you to get your gear over what the average is in the guild? I don't know, maybe you don't wanna get better gear. Maybe that other caster couldn't afford the robe you could? <br>
<br>
Also you'll take note in my post that i don't know about necro items and that I was assuming they were the same. I noted that you said thurg robes were about the same as ss robes or kael robes, and I know that pog items are just like thurg items, with the stat bonuses switched a bit(as melee gear goes).<br>
<br>
<br>
Diamonds are neither 50kpp nor hard to get. Lets assume a guild gets 2 green dragon scales up there. Warrior a is at the raid, and is the only warrior at the raid. The rest fell off, and bounced on the chain on the way down. He is near or at this step in his quest. There are several other warriors who are close to this step in guild who are not there. Would we sell this hard to get item, random it off to someone who could sell it, or would we hold it?<br>
<br>
As for your cleric example, again, if you are as active as you're saying this cleric is in your example, you will raid him often. He will get more gear than the other clerics who play less because he is there more to get it.<br>
