<br>
I think there is a vast difference in a dropped item that less than 1% of a class will ever have(from the stats I assume that came from ubermob_00whatever, but i don't look up loot tables from such mobs to drool over, so i am not familiar with who drops it) compared to a time consuming quest available to all members of a class after level 50. <br>
<br>
For example, when you put together a raid on a triggered spawn for guildmate x(and guildmate x has spent a good deal of time to get to the point they could trigger it), it's a little different that hitting a zone and having something drop for 2 people that have the same time in guild(blah blah blah, they're even).<br>
<br>
&quot;As for the new Ferrari. Who would deserve it more, the guy who already has a Jaguar who bought it with the money from his second job that he worked at nights for, or the guy who barely held down his day job and drives a Datsun &quot;Honey-Bee&quot; to guild raids once a month?&quot;<br>
<br>
What happens when two people put forth the same amount of work at job 1, but person A works a second job to get a ferrari? Does person A deserve to have 2 ferraris before person B has a single one? They both work just as hard for the company. Let's assume they race their cars for a living.<br>
<br>
Solution 1.<br>
person A says &quot;ya know this model is a year newer, I'll flip you for it, if i win you can have my older ferrari&quot;<br>
<br>
Solution 2.<br>
Employer says &quot;well, person A likes his car, and to be honest it seems a little strange to be giving someone who put forth no more effort for our company than B here a second good car before B gets an upgrade from his geo metro.&quot;<br>
<br>
Solution 3.<br>
Employer says &quot;Person A gets the ferrari, his second. This is because it is in our companies best interest to keep him in the latest model ferrari, even though he already has one and even though you don't own a competitive car at all yet Mr B&quot;<br>
<br>
Which solution seems to be the most fair and sensible?<br>
<br>
&quot;Similarly, you've made it clear that as an ALT, he'd never, ever, loot ahead of a main? What situation will he get more gear than the other clerics in?&quot;<br>
<br>
Lets say your guild raids hate 20 times in a 6 month period. Your alt is there for every raid, and so are 2 of your guildmate clerics(these people are raiding just as much as your secondary char, if not more). There are also 2 clerics who show up now and then, and have made 5 raids each. Your alt gets anything the main characters pass on. Is it really hard to believe that out of 20 raids you won't have more than the 2 who made it to 1 raid in 4?<br>
<br>
&quot;It's finally obvious to me what you don't understand. (Or what you pretend not to...) You know we all raid the same amount, but I will get the best equipment because the GUILD is more import &quot;<br>
<br>
Who decides how much either has put into the guild?  Who chooses which is more important? How do you do that if they both put the same time and effort into the guild? More importantly, how do you do so without spreading ill will around? Putting a lot of time into a guild(as much as anyone else of your class) and being told &quot;You get the leftovers&quot; could be seen as, pardon me for saying it, &quot;A slap in the face.&quot;.<br>
<br>
 If your system works for you, great. I prefer mine to it and these are just some of the examples why. They might be reasons that justify your system to you, however  your system is not the only way, and neither is mine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utreistaania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>treistaania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/02 2:10:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=818.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, then.</span><hr size=1> outfitting your bards necros paladins and clerics etc etc is just as important as outfitting the main tank..<br>
