Someone help me out here.<br>
<br>
For every guild the size of mine, the &quot;MA Tanking&quot; strategy is a necessity.  To not outfit a warrior (or a small group of warriors) ahead of the curve of equipment in your guild only decreases the overall ability of your guild to raise the average level of equipment in your guild.<br>
<br>
Every tank in Vision has better equipment because they sacrificed in this SHORT TERM for the LONG TERM benefit of equipping Allamar as best as possible.<br>
<br>
Having 20 mediocre dressed warriors is no substitute for 1 VERY WELL dressed warrior and 19 nearly-as-mediocre warriors.<br>
<br>
I do not care what strategy your guild, or any other guild on this server uses; but to stand up repeated and say that it doesn't make sense to equip Allamar first only shows that you don't understand how some encounters in the game MUST work. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
