<br>
It only makes sense if you're aiming for a more time efficient method of improving the guild.  Crist0's attitude toward the game appears to be that everyone should have a chance at a reward if they put in work.  Sure it may take ten times as long but eventually your MT will be outfitted just as well as if you funnelled all loot to him in the first place -- it will simply take longer.  Remember, loot in this game doesn't rot from time or use! A different attitude toward playing the game doesn't make someone wrong.  They're willing to wait the extra 3 or 4 years it might take using /random before their MA is outfitted.  Why criticize someone for playing the game differently?<br>
<br>
As to your rhetorical question, guilds now at the top do MT loot first because it's the quickest way to the top.  Guilds that do totally random loot (or some other loot style) are likely still working their way up the chain.  Within 10 years or so though the landscape will be different and we can revisit your question at that time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uxeck.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xeck</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/02 7:35:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=818.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Your both right!</span><hr size=1> Your both right!  Here is why:<br>
<br>
Outfitting the MT is the best way to go IF that warrior is always there for the raids.<br>
If the MT is dealing with RL stuff, your raid is going to have to get along with a lesser equipped replacement than if you randomed.  <br>
<br>
So before a guild can go to the more efficient method of loot distribution, it must have a VERY reliable MT.<br>
<br>
If the MT isn't available, the raid is in deep trouble.<br>
